description:
All stories in this anthology have been (co-)written by Jesse Young. He invited several artists to do the artwork and got funding for his book through Kickstarter.

From the back cover:

'Here We Go' is a collection of short comics written by Jesse Young. Spanning genres from the 19th century action/adventure 'Ex Occultus' to the sci-fi epic 'The Daring Adventures of Android Jones' to the Pixar-esque 'Here We Go', Young takes readers on a journey through imagination and leaves them wanting more.

Stories collected in this volume are:

  • Here We Go
  • Forbidden Love
  • The Silver Street Boys
  • The Daring Adventures of Android Jones - Chapter 1
  • Uncle Buck
  • Ex Occultus, The Sword of Peleus
  • The Devil You Know
  • He's Heating Up
  • The Daring Adventures of Android Jones - Chapter 2

The book ends with 'Collaborator' pages that holds introductions on all the artists that participated in this anthology and a thank you page for all the backers.

The final showdown between the world’s greatest warrior and comics’ biggest idiot! Conan fights for his kingdom, Groo fights for his bakery, and Sergio and Mark fight for their comic shop . . . Triple story lines collide in a chaotic climax of barbaric proportions!
name: Chapter Four

description:
No one captures the horror and misery of war like GARTH ENNIS! The horrors of WW2 bomber pilots faced were so much greater than simply the enemy fire. The mettle of a man gets tested in many ways in a conflict of that scale. Ennis proves time and time again that in battle it isn't the technology or the weapons you wield, but the fire within that leads to the ultimate outcome on the battlefield. Available with Regular, Wraparound, Good Girl Nose Art, and Battle Damage Retailer Incentive covers by Matt Martin.

description: With the return of STRAY BULLETS, it's time to roll out the "by story arc" trades of DAVID LAPHAM's influential crime masterpiece.... These are their stories. Follow the lost lives of people who are savagely torn apart by events beyond their control. As the innocent world of an imaginative little girl is shattered when she witnesses a brutal double murder. Or an introverted young boy on the verge of manhood gets a lesson on just how far is too far when he falls for a needy woman who lives life in the fast lane. Or party with a pair of low-rent hoods who learn about what is really important in life just when they shouldn't. And even learn the story of the most infamous gangster who ever lived, Amy Racecar, who talks to God, lunches with the President, and just may be responsible for the end of the world. These are some of the tales that will rip out your guts and break your heart. Collects STRAY BULLETS #1-7.
name: Volume One

description: "Jumpin' jacksnipes!" Duckburg's richest tycoon is on the hunt for legendary square eggs — and he's bringing Donald, Huey, Dewey, and Louie along! It’s our second complete, chronological book of Duck adventures by internationally celebrated fan favorite Don Rosa — following in the footsteps of Disney legend Carl Barks with his own distinctive style! Famed for his prizewinning Life and Times of Scrooge McDuck, Rosa wrote and drew two decades' worth of ripping Duck yarns and is among the world's most beloved modern cartoonists. Star stories in our second Rosa book include "Return to Plain Awful," Rosa’s sequel to Barks' "Lost in the Andes." Then, in "His Majesty McDuck," Scrooge beats the IRS by seceding from the Union... only to have his new country colonized by the Beagle Boys! Plus more! Presented with a rich archive of Rosa's cover art and behind-the-scenes factoids, these Duckburg epics are getting a definitive, comprehensive North American edition for the very first time — at a bargain price worthy of Scrooge himself!
name: Vol. 2

volume.name: Walt Disney's Uncle Scrooge and Donald Duck: Return to Plain Awful

description:
All Hallowed Love

In upstate New York in 1868, an overbearing mother and absent farm scarcely fill the void for Sophia Baukker. As Sophia desperately searches for her young lover she encounters the hypnotic guile of Satan. On this fateful night, Sophia is pulled by the forewarning of her mother and the spellbinding promises of an ancient witch; each clamoring for the possession of her soul.
name: All Hallowed Love

description: It's a Halloween special. A boy who admires Batman decides to become the Caped Crusader and stop some neighborhood bullies.
name: Chapter Forty-Six

description:
Cale and his team are reluctantly pulled back into the Military as Hurricane Brandon pushes through the desert of the Southwest gaining strength and leaving wide path of destruction. To save the country the President faces the hardest decision of her life.

Artwork by Dennis Calero (X-Men Noir)

Note: The digital edition (10/29/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Utopia

Bound by the Infinite, Porter is forced to watch his life replay before his eyes, beginning with his inglorious birth. Some things he hadn't been able to understand while he lived, and others he'd forgotten.

"Apple don't fall too far from th' tree I guess."

Porter's childhood launches with twin tales of good intentions foiled by the deeds of others and the shortcomings of mortality. The clock is ticking...
name: Utopia

description:
Intelligent Design - Part 1

The Civil Four head from the ashes of Washington D.C. to the hustle and bustle of New York City. The team takes up residence in "The Black House". Built to protect the President from threats dark and unearthly. Will this house of mystery offer protection or end up their tomb?
name: Intelligent Design Part 1

description:
Me, My Poodle, and a Shopping Fix

A woman and her poodle go shopping.
name: Me, My Poodle, and A Shopping Fix

description: The anticipated climax of the well received reimagined Doian Gray story- Now that Dorian understands his role, he realized that he has to fight for the soul of the girl he loves in one last knockdown, drag out fight with the demons.

'To Become A Monster' Part One

Freddie was betrayed by his country. They turned him into something non-human and used him as a weapon. Bobby betrayed his country. They then made him their test subject for a new advancement serum.

Bobby must obey orders and bide his time, waiting for the chance to get out of his solitary. Freddie must fight back and be vigilant, saving Bobby before he becomes just like him.
name: To Become A Monster Part One

description: Gear up in your best costume and ring that doorbell, 'cause we've got a bagful of GD goodies for you! Your favorite cast members dress up and party or case the neighbors for getting tasty treats or pulling high-tech pranks!
The battered resistance regroups in the Tower of Fate while the status of the long missing Wonder Woman is revealed.
name: Chapter Five: The Coin

volume.name: Injustice: Gods Among Us Year Three

description: What will become of our rodent pals? Find out in this thrilling conclusion!

Pewfell and his companions have penetrated the castle lair of Hornia, Witch Queen of the Scraper Mountains, in order to retrieve the mysterious artifact known as the "Heart of Crwm". Of course things do not go well and, before long, both Pewfell and Bish are at the mercy the many tentacled succubus.
After a bad vacation experience, Princezz and her blubbery royal-aide return to the castle. Gun fights and fisticuffs take center stage in this spectacular outlaw issue!

Escaping the SS Satanic with Rebecca in the Grim Reaper, Requiem flies into the heart of the Dragon Blitz. Thurim - a Teutonic Knight and Requiem's previous incarnation - can wait in the shadows no longer: he seizes control of Requiem and the fighter plane to beat back the attack, and takes on Otto in daring aerial combat.

As Count Dracula and Nero observe the dogfight from the deck of the SS Satanic, they come under bombardment from Gotha Dragon Bombers, who carry a particularly unpleasant payload. With the psychic teams strained to the limit, dwindling supplies of Black Opium are essential to maintain defenses. But the Black Opium emergency supply train is about to have unexpected visitors dropping in...

Volume 5 also introduces Necropolis's most charming and seductive vampire: Count Sabre Eretica, a dandy whose love of fine things is only surpassed by his love of fine women...
name: Dragon Blitz

description: There's no slowing down in the aftermath of the shocking conclusion to Sanctuary's first arc, "Fresh Meat." Now issue #8 find Dr. Pierre with a kettle-full of trouble with a kidnapping, a pile of dead birds, cheap wine, a room full of uneaten vegetables, and a shapeshifter? Wait, what book is this?
Hippolyta’s first rule of war is demonstrated in “Generations,” as Diana and Cheetah battle over a phoenix egg – and its promise of immortality!
name: Generations Part 1

description: Superman has defeated the Monitors, but what steps can he possibly take to keep the universe safe from them in the future?
name: Chapter Ten

description:
Don and Kenny's world gets blown wide open as they jump from the frying pan into the fire: evilBay, magic, dolphin sex and more.

What's a boy and his monkey to do?

And who the hell is Anubis Jones?

The physically-disabied children experimented on by Dr. Epstein are all grown up with unexpected side-effects: powers. Now they are out in the world an on the run from the ruthless organization bent on controlling their incredible abilities. Some have grouped together for survival, but not everyone is on the same side.

When Armageddon begins and hordes of demons invade the Earth, five orphaned siblings suddenly find themselves in the care of an enigmatic, gruff looking magician who identifies himself only as Mr. Rhee. He has vowed to protect them, but is there anywhere truly safe - or anyone truly trustworthy - when the world is ending?
From November 1954, "The Forbidden Forest": Spaceships are crashing because pilots have space blindness due to lack of Vita Q, an element harvested in the swamps of Venus.

The groundbreaking digital comic returns! Half a million downloads, and the inspiration for everything from Thrillbent itself to comics like Moth City! Read where it all began! Repelled by Roland and Gloriana's attitudes and their use of magic, Valentine plans escape from the Dawn Country. But in his haste, he makes a significant mistake of understanding.. and the Earth he returns to is not the one he left.

What are the mysterious "shadow creatures" after? Anne Howard and "vine boy" ponder this question as they seek to evade their pursuers. But soon they are faced with a dilemma. Should they flee to safer climes... or stay to help others who are in danger?

VINE is a new comic series in the Tarzan/Indiana Jones tradition of exotic action adventure, with an added dose of Tolkienesque fantasy and romance!

Searching for a tributary that will return him to the present while adrift in the time stream, Witch Hunter lands in ancient Byzantium and finds himself at the mercy of Empress Theodora. Caught between dark elves and angry witches being persecuted by the royal court, he needs to find a weapon powerful enough to overthrow the current regime or be prepared to die in 535 A.D. at the hands of those he's trying to save!
name: Spellbound In Byzantium
